The paper deals with compressing human motion capture data, which involves analyzing and processing sequences of movements. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Graphics (cs.GR), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), or Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on developing a tailored transform coding algorithm for mocap data, it is most likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible because they involve similar techniques and applications, but they are less likely because they are not as directly related to the paper's main contribution.
